name: lib/gulp-graph.js
GulpGraph
description:
The GulpGraph is the child implementation that contains the actual AST parsing
logic for initialization

name: assemblegraph
description: Assembles the initial graph from the source JavaScript gulpfile

name: defineTask
description: Function to initially define a task when reading from JavaScript string

params.name: task_name
params.description: the name of the task to define

params.name: task_ast
params.description: tree of the task's function, if it calls one, else null

name: defineSubTask
description: TODO: Function that assembles the graph of the gulp task's sub routines

params.name: parent
params.description: the gulp task that the subroutine belongs to

name: lib/gulp-nodes.js
TaskNode
description: TaskNodes represent a gulp task in the GulpGraph

name: constructor
description:
TaskNodes are constructed from an initialization object and
the parent graph to link task dependencies on and add itself to.

name: linkDependencies
description:
function to create edges on parent graph between self and
dependent tasks

params.name: parent_graph
params.description: the parent graph to link to TaskNodes on

name: PackageNode
description: TaskNodes represent an imported package in the GulpGraph

name: constructor
description:
PackageNodes are constructed from an initialization object and
the parent graph to link task dependencies on and add itself to.

params.name: init.identifier
params.description: the variable name the package is assigned to

name: identifier
description: exposes the PackageNode's identifier

name: lib/interface.js
setPair
description:
Helper function for conveniently setting object properties with
key value pairs like:
```javascript
  let pair = [ key, value ];
```

params.name: property
params.description: the the object to assign the pair on

name: GulpNode
description:
the GulpNode interface is intended as an abstract class for
the GulpGraph Nodes to inherit

name: constructor
description:
The GulpNode is constructed from an object, allowing its child classes
to have different initialization properties. Requires a name, defaults
type to 'GulpNode'

name: addSelf
description:
used by some children classes to add themselves to the JointGraph.GRAPH
at the end of initialization.

params.name: graph
params.description: the parent graph for the node to add itself to

name: label
description:
Static getter for the label, which is of the form:
```javascript
type.toLowerCase() + ':' + name.toLowerCase
```

name: JointGraph
description:
the JointGraph interface is intended as an abstract class for
the GulpGraph to inherit

name: constructor
description:
The JointGraph wraps a graphlib object, a js string,
a dependencies array, and a config object

name: config
description:
Set a graph config variable for the whole gulpgraph from an array pair
like:
```javascript
  let pair = [ key, value ];
```

name: dependencies
description:
Set a graph dependency for the whole gulpgraph from an array pair
like:
```javascript
  let pair = [ key, value ];
```

name: toJSON
description: Represents the current GulpGraph as Json

name: toDOT
description:
Represents the current GulpGraph using the DOT plain-text
graph description language
